# Code Review Guidelines

Run `git diff HEAD` or `git diff --staged` first. Review full file context, not just the diff.

## Review checklist

**Quality**: clear and self-documenting, SRP, no duplication, meaningful names
**Correctness**: error handling for all paths, edge cases (null, empty, boundary), no off-by-one
**Security**: no exposed secrets, input validation, injection prevention, proper auth checks
**Performance**: no N+1 queries, no unnecessary recomputation, appropriate caching
**Testing**: new behavior has coverage, tests are meaningful (not just padding)

## Output priority
🚨 Critical (block merge) → ⚠️ Warning (should fix) → 💡 Suggestion (consider)

Include code snippets showing the fix for critical and warning items.
